Male: FW dorsal field (
Fig. 7C
) translucent brown with yellow veins, its antero-lateral corner with a large whitish sclerotization; area of plectrum with a strong orange sclerotization. Vein 1A bisinuate anterior to angle. File with 116 stridulatory teeth distributed on transverse part of 1A (107) and on angle (9) (n=1). CuA barely curved inward. CuP absent. Mirror not rounded but well differentiated from other cells of D alignment, forming a wide rectangle. Cell c1 not widened posteriorly, without transverse vein. Apical field short, with faint reticulated veins posterior to mirror (cell alignment E). Lateral field homogeneously dark brown (veins and cells); veins R and M strong, delimiting a darker area; Sc with one preapical projection. Lateral field with five (n=1) strong parallel longitudinal veins ventral to Sc, with faint dark transverse veins.
